{"questionId":"33085231","questionHtml":"<p>For a particular arithmetic sequence,&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>25</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> such that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>k</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;or&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> &nbsp; or &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; to set up at least one equation in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>d</mi></math> &nbsp; and &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>24</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to solve their two linear equations in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> simultaneously (must eliminate one variable)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>⇒</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>52</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>k</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> with their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> (or with their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33085231","referenceCode":"24N.1.AHL.TZ0.5","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"For a particular arithmetic sequence, u10=16 and S25=100. Find the value of k such that uk=0.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"5","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}